history.content: From my experience, CS 70 usually expands enough to accommodate most people.

On classes.berkeley.edu, it states that there are 90 open seats and 112 waitlisted for CS 70 in the Fall. Originally, I was planning on taking 70 over the summer, but decided to drop and take it during the school year. Thus, I have not added it to my Fall 2018 schedule yet (my Phase II has not began yet).

Will CS 70 expand to accomodate all students interested in taking the class? Or is it more likely that the class won't expand and I'll only get in if other students drop?
history.subject: CS 70 Class Expansion?
